#note the question here is whether to sacrifice points to open the board with OOT (I thought about POOT also), or to play OPE at N10 and wait. In hindsight, I would definitely choose OPE. Opening the top-left is great, but I score so little in the process that Tarin can likely block and put himself up by 70-80 points. With OPE at N10, I would only be down 34, close enough that Tarin can't sacrifice points to block row 14. I also have a nice fish I can make next turn if I need to - just QI at G9 setting up QIN as a bingo lane. Of course, the downside is that if Tarin can block row 14, I'll be down 40-50 on a completely dead board, but I think that's a risk worth taking here.
